<https://w3id.org/ontologies-ULL/OSDi#hasSensitivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Sensitivity in epidemiology is the Probability of correctly classifying a sick individual, that is, the Probability that a positive result will be obtained in a diagnostic test for a sick subject. The Sensitivity is, therefore, the ability of the complementary test to detect the disease. Sensitivity is the percentage of true positives or the Probability that the test is positive if the disease is present; False negatives are sick subjects diagnosed as healthy." .
<https://w3id.org/ontologies-ULL/OSDi#hasSensitivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has sensitivity"@en .
