<https://w3id.org/ontologies-ULL/OSDi#hasOffsetParameter> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Defines the offset parameter of a probability distribution, which is a value that is added to the random variable defined by the distribution. This is useful for defining distributions that can only take values above or below a certain threshold (for example, an offset of 1 in a Poisson distribution would define a distribution that can only take values from 1 to infinite, instead of from 0 to infinite)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ontologies-ULL/OSDi#hasOffsetParameter> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has offset parameter"@en .
